strategy: Combine single-pass aggregation with column pruning and parallel dimension processing: First, pre-aggregate each fact table at the key level (date_sk, item_sk) with counts and sums, applying NULL filt
what_failed: Regression (0.73x): Pre-aggregated each fact table by sold_date_sk and item_sk with counts and sums before any joins, created compact dimension CTEs with only needed columns, then joined the aggregated facts with dimensions in parallel UNION ALL branches. This reduces fact table rows before expensive joins and minimizes dimension table reprocessing.
why_it_failed: Created year-specific CTEs (store_sales_1999, store_sales_2000, etc.) but KEPT the original year_total union CTE alongside them. The optimizer materializes both the split versions and the original union, resulting in redundant computation. Projection cardinality estimates show 10^16x errors from the confused CTE graph.
